{"id":61569,"title":"Personalized platelet transfusions: one step closer to the clinic.","abstract":"In this issue of Cell Stem Cell, Nakamura et al. (2014) use human pluripotent stem cells to generate immortalized megakaryocyte progenitor cell lines that can be cryopreserved, expanded in vitro, and induced to undergo terminal maturation and platelet release. This strategy advances efforts to produce clinically relevant numbers of tissue-culture-derived platelets for transfusion therapies.","date":"2014-04-07","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24702993","annotations":[{"name":"Platelet","weight":0.822622,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Platelet"},{"name":"Cell culture","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_culture"},{"name":"In vitro","weight":0.785202,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In_vitro"},{"name":"Cell (biology)","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_(biology)"},{"name":"Stem cell","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stem_cell"},{"name":"Pluripotent","weight":0.76489,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pluripotent"},{"name":"Cryopreservation","weight":0.755917,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryopreservation"},{"name":"Blood transfusion","weight":0.723023,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_transfusion"},{"name":"Progenitor cell","weight":0.712945,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Progenitor_cell"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.667165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.42438,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Megakaryocyte","weight":0.327124,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Megakaryocyte"},{"name":"Clinic","weight":0.287896,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinic"},{"name":"In